      • reuseIterator

        Iterator<Entry> reuseIterator()
        Returns the same iterator as List.iterator() with the only difference that it reuses Entry objects when calling Iterator.next(). Hence, this method should only be used if references to Entry objects are only kept and accesed until the next Iterator.next() call.
